THEORY 
Introduction to WordPress 
WordPress is an open-source Content Management System (CMS) used to create and 
manage websites without extensive programming knowledge. It is widely adopted for 
blogs, business websites, portfolios, and digital marketing projects due to its flexibility, 
ease of use, and large ecosystem. In digital marketing, WordPress is used to: 
● 
Publish optimized content 
● 
Support SEO activities 
● 
Integrate social media platforms 
● 
Track visitor behavior
Plugin-Based Architecture of WordPress 
WordPress follows a plugin-based architecture where additional features can be added 
through plugins. A plugin is a software extension that enhances website functionality 
without modifying the WordPress core. 
Plugins allow marketers and developers to adapt websites according to marketing 
goals such as visibility, engagement, and performance tracking. 








Result 
